This paper is primarily focused on image captioning, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. However, the paper also deals with language translation and fluency estimation, which are natural language processing (NLP) tasks falling under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel learning framework, which involves training an image captioning model using machine-translated sentences, which is an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) task. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on bilingual datasets, which is a multimedia (cs.MM) task. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM, in that order.
